The paper discusses strategies for handling context-sensitive features in supervised machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and software engineering (cs.SE). The focus on supervised learning suggests that cs.LG is the most likely category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CL. The mention of recovering lost contextual information also suggests a connection to cs.CV, while the discussion of different strategies for handling context sensitivity is relevant to cs.SE.
